2 Method 2.1 Participants and Data Preprocessing We used 203 subjects (50AD / 27pMCI / 42sMCI / 34SMC / 50NC) from ADNI dataset (http://adni.loni.usc.edu/).
The preprocessing pipeline is as follows: for T1 image, we applied skull removal, segmentation via FreeSurfer (https://surfer.nmr.mgh.harvard.edu/) package and ROI labeling by Destrieux Atlas.

For rs-fMRI image, we applied spatial smoothing, slice time correction, temporal pre-whitening, global drift removal and band pass filtering (0.01-0.1 Hz) using FEAT command in FMRIB Software Li-brary (FSL) (https://fsl.fmrib.ox.ac.uk/fsl/fslwiki/).
All images are single- channel, 512x512, and available online at https://people.csail.mit.edu/lebrandt.
